root_causes: OE presence check uses A1x1_9 > 0 and A1x1_9 < 97 to exclude special codes, which incorrectly excludes valid counts >= 97 (e.g. 100). It should explicitly exclude only the special codes (97,98,99).

OE-negative-case (text present but count missing/zero) does not explicitly exclude special codes. While a special code won't be missing, the intent in comments is to never flag when the cell contains a special code; the check should explicitly exclude special codes to match the comment/intent.

Potential mismatch with 'NotRequired': per-cell validation flags miss(x) as an error when flt_A1x1 = 1. The expected attributes include NotRequired = true; if cells are truly optional then missing should not be flagged. (If the intended logic is to require every cell when the column applies then current behavior is OK.)
instructions: Replace the OE-required condition: change (not missing(A1x1_9) and A1x1_9 > 0 and A1x1_9 < 97) to (not missing(A1x1_9) and A1x1_9 > 0 and not (A1x1_9 in (97,98,99))). This will require OE text for any positive numeric count while excluding only the special codes 97/98/99.

Change the OE-negative-case condition to explicitly exclude special codes. For example: sel if flt_A1x1 = 1 and ((missing(A1x1_9) or A1x1_9 = 0) and not (A1x1_9 in (97,98,99))) and (not missing(A1x1_9_other) and A1x1_9_other <> ''). Or more clearly: sel if flt_A1x1 = 1 and ( (missing(A1x1_9) or A1x1_9 = 0) ) and (not (A1x1_9 in (97,98,99))) and (not missing(A1x1_9_other) and A1x1_9_other <> '').

Review the per-cell missing-value behavior against the 'NotRequired' attribute. If cells should be optional when the column applies, remove miss(x) from the per-cell invalid condition (i.e. only flag when present but out of range). If cells must be provided when the column applies, keep miss(x) as currently implemented.
